HEADWORD: Well-seen
<hw>Well"-seen`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having seen much;
hence, accomplished; experienced.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Well-seen</qex> in arms and proved in many a fight.</q>
